<TITLE> Stocks down again on profit-taking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 17 (bdnews24.com)Markets ended down Tuesday for the second straight day as profit-taking dominated the day's trading. The DSE general index also fell on post-dividend trade and a price adjustment for Mercantile Bank. Turnover on the prime bourse also tumbled to below Tk 5 billion from above Tk 6 billion at the start of the week. The opening session saw gains on a surge in Prime Finance First Mutual Fund, which started trading Tuesday. "The mutual fund went up more than 600 percent, which is quite natural in this market on a scrip's debut," an official of brokerage firm Anwar Securities said. But post-dividend trade, Mercantile Bank's price adjustment, along with profit-taking, caused the general index to fall steeply in midday trade, he added. Market observers said the day's trading was healthy. "Trading was perfectly normal, with investor participation on the rise," Saiful Islam, the senior vice-president of DSE said. Indices down The DGEN or general index ended on 2637.99, losing 15.11 points or 0.56 percent. The DSI or all share price index finished 12.75 points or 0.57 percent lower at 2194.94. The bourse's blue-chip DSE-20 shed 15.45 points or 0.72.18 percent to 2102.25. Losers outnumbered gainers 169 to 82 while seven issues held steady. Indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange fell due to losses in banks, pharmaceuticals and paper shares. The CSCX or selective categories index fell 42.27 points or 0.79 percent to close at 5246.84. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8133.94, down by 61.43 points or 0.74 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip index plunged 49.97 points or 0.76 percent to finish at 6443.06. Of the traded issues, 116 declined, 50 advanced with three scrips remaining unchanged. Turnover tumbles The prime bourse's turnover tumbled to Tk 4.96 billion, with 34,312, 630 shares trading hands from the previous day's Tk 5.57 billion. Turnover on the Chittagong Stock Exchange reached Tk 623.661 million from the trading of 6,802,011 shares traded  down from Monday's Tk 760.800 million. DSE's top ten by turnover Prime Finance First Mutual Fund, on its debut, topped the turnover board with shares worth Tk 368.51 million changing hands The fund price opened at Tk 55 and went as high as Tk. 78.80. It closed at Tk 71.60. Summit Power with a turnover of Tk 218.558 million ended on Tk 1025, gaining 1.35 percent after falling Monday. Summit Alliance Port Ltd shrugged off the previous day's losses to end on Tk 1749.25, surging 12.47 percent Beximco Pharmaceuticals with shares traded worth Tk 178.352 million; it lost 1.04 percent to Tk 161.70. Beximco followed it to rise 1.10 percent at Tk 192.90. Powergrid Company of Bangladesh rose 2.29 percent to finish at Tk 557.25. The other scrips on the turnover board Apex Adelchi Footwear, Beximco Synthetics, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and S Alam Cold Rolled Steels ended higher. State-owned Titas Gas fell as investors locked in profits.
